---
title: Shawarma-Spiced Mushrooms & Tofu with Cabbage & Carrot Salad, Hummus, White Sauce & Pitas
description: This mezze-inspired array of bites creates a flavorful vegetarian meal perfect for any day of the week. Hearty portobello mushrooms are sautéed with onion wedges and seasoned with our shawarma spice blend. Alongside is a fresh, tangy salad of red cabbage and carrot, velvety hummus, toasted pita breads, and a lemony white sauce for drizzling.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6772d02f555c15a993e57004-3db14f4d.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67742ba9893e50c2a80a57d9-en-US.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 770 kcal
  fat: 40 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 65 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 30 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 870 mg
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/shawarma-spiced-mushrooms-and-tofu-67742ba9893e50c2a80a57d9
servings: 2
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: Middle East
---

Wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Halve, peel, and cut @onion{1} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Using the tip of a #spoon{}, remove and discard black gills from undersides of @portobello mushrooms{2}; cut into 1⁄2-inch-thick strips.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%ounce}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}, juice from half the lemon, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{} until thoroughly combined. Refrigerate until ready to use.

> For 4 servings, use 1 tsp sugar and juice from whole lemon.

Open and drain @tofu{1}, then press out excess water with #paper towels{} and cut into 3⁄4-inch cubes. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Using a #spatula{}, arrange into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tofu is browned all over, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}; wipe out pan.

> You can substitute chicken* for tofu here if preferred. Cook chicken until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until starting to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add another large drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} and mushrooms to pan. Season with half the @shawarma spice blend{1%tablespoon}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Reduce heat to medium low and cover. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> You may need to cook in batches for 4 servings. Use pan used for tofu or chicken here.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @yogurt{2%tablespoon}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, and as much lemon zest as you like. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Toast @pitas{2} until golden brown, then cut into quarters.

Divide veggies, @Sabra® Classic Hummus{4%tablespoon}, salad, and pitas between plates in separate sections. Serve with white sauce on the side.

> TIP: Enjoy with your favorite hot sauce if you like things spicy!